<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-1128] MAC OS X: thrift.h incompatibility with Thrift.h</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-1128</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The default filesystem on Mac OS X is case-insensitive&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If thrift is compiled with c_glib support, upon install, the &quot;thrift.h&quot; installed by c_glib trumps the classical &quot;Thrift.h&quot; C++ header.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;C++ apps afterwards fail to compile (for obvious reasons).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Had to re-compile+install libthrift &lt;b&gt;without&lt;/b&gt; c_glib support to get back the original contents of Thrift.h needed for C++ support&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Mac OS X 10.6.7&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
        <key id="12503215">THRIFT-1128</key>
